## What Is a 'Domain Name'?

Domain names keep the really technical IP address invisible for most viewers, is Not the Same as URL. A URL goes into much more detail than domain name, providing much more information, including the specific page address, folder name, machine name, and protocol language. Example of an URL (Uniform Resource Locator), with their domain names bolded: http://www.serverpoint.com/en/dedicated-server

Customers can register domain either as part of the order process for shared hosting accounts, or in their control panel whenever they have such need. Prices per domain vary depending on the extension (.com .name .info etc).
